ite sugar\n- 1 teaspoon of active dry yeast\n- 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil\n- 1 teaspoon of salt\n- 2 cups of warm water\n\nInstructions:\n\n1. In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, yeast, oil, and salt.\n2. Gradually stir in warm water until a soft dough forms.\n3. Knead the dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth, about 10 minutes.\n4. Place the dough back in the bowl and cover with a damp cloth. Let the dough rise until doubled in size, about 1 hour.\n5. Punch the dough down and divide into 12 equal pieces.\n6. Roll each piece into a ball and cover with a damp cloth. Let the balls rest for about 10 minutes.\n7. Flatten each ball into a disk about 6 inches in diameter.\n8. Heat a lightly oiled skillet over medium heat.\n9. Place the canjeero disks in the skillet and cook for about 2 minutes. Flip and cook for another 2 minutes.\n10. Serve warm and enjoy!","generator":"text-davinci-003","sample_mode":"temp=0.7,top_p=1.0,max_new_tokens=300","dataset":"helpful_base","datasplit":"eval"},"truncated_cells":[]},{"row_idx":13,"row":{"instruction":"What are the best exercises for beginners?","input":"","output":"Some of the best exercises for beginners are walking, jogging, cycling, and swimming. These activities are great for building endurance and helping you stay active. Other beginner exercises include squats, lunges, planks, and crunches. These exercises can help you build strength and improve your overall fitness level.","generator":"text-davinci-003","sample_mode":"temp=0.7,top_p=1.0,max_new_tokens=300","dataset":"helpful_base","datasplit":"eval"},"truncated_cells":[]},{"row_idx":14,"row":{"instruction":"Do you know why turkeys became the official food of thanksgiving?","input":"","output":"According to historians, it is believed that wild turkeys were most likely a part of the first Thanksgiving feast in 1621, based on accounts from the pilgrims. Turkeys have been associated with the holiday ever since.","generator":"text-davinci-003","sample_mode"