l each piece of dough into a long, thin rope and braid the three ropes together. \n8. Place the challah on a greased baking sheet and let it rise for another hour.\n9. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.\n10. Brush the challah with a beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame or poppy seeds.","generator":"text-davinci-003","sample_mode":"temp=0.7,top_p=1.0,max_new_tokens=300","dataset":"helpful_base","datasplit":"eval"},"truncated_cells":[]},{"row_idx":93,"row":{"instruction":"Did Facebook corporation change its name?","input":"","output":"No, Facebook did not change its name.","generator":"text-davinci-003","sample_mode":"temp=0.7,top_p=1.0,max_new_tokens=300","dataset":"helpful_base","datasplit":"eval"},"truncated_cells":[]},{"row_idx":94,"row":{"instruction":"I like to host guests at my home from time to time, and I am gathering  recipes of different dishes and drinks to keep things interesting. I am interested in trying some Hong Kong  dishes. Can you give me a recipe for Tong Sui?","input":"","output":"Sure, here is a recipe for Tong Sui, a popular Hong Kong dessert: \n\nIngredients:\n\n-2 tablespoons of glutinous rice flour\n-3 tablespoons of sugar\n-2 cups of water\n-1/4 teaspoon of salt\n-Assorted fruits (optional)\n\nInstructions:\n\n1. In a bowl, mix the glutinous rice flour and sugar together.\n\n2. In a saucepan over medium heat, bring the water and salt to a boil.\n\n3. Gradually stir in the flour and sugar mixture until it thickens.\n\n4. Reduce the heat to low and cook for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.\n\n5. Serve warm and top with assorted fruits if desired. Enjoy!","generator":"text-davinci-003","sample_mode":"temp=0.7,top_p=1.0,max_new_tokens=300","dataset":"helpful_base","datasplit":"eval"},"truncated_cells":[]},{"row_idx":95,"row":{"instruction":"I want to start saving some money by growing my own food. Can I do this during the winter with an indoor garden?","input":"","output":"Yes, it is possible to grow an indoor garden even in the